  .container
    .row.page-header
      .col-lg-12.text-center
        h1(style="color: white;") Welcome to the World of Cybersecurity
        p Explore the World of Cybersecurity and Its Importance
      
      .col-lg-6.text-center
        img(src="https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/msid-93867928,imgsize-34558,width-1200,height=765,overlay-etciosea/news/security/cybersecurity-market-worth-usd-266-billion-by-2027-report.jpg", alt="Cybersecurity Illustration", style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;")

    .row.about-cybersecurity
      .col-lg-6
        h2(style="color: white;") What is Cybersecurity?
        p.large-font
          | Cybersecurity is the practice of protecting computer systems, networks, and data from theft, damage, or unauthorized access. It encompasses a range of technologies, processes, and practices designed to safeguard digital information and ensure the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data.

    .row.importance
      .col-lg-12
        h2(style="color: white;") Why Cybersecurity Matters
        p.large-font
          | Cybersecurity is vital in today's interconnected world. With the increasing reliance on technology, the potential threats to digital assets and privacy have also grown. Effective cybersecurity measures are crucial to protect against cyberattacks, data breaches, and unauthorized access to sensitive information.

    .row.career-opportunities
      .col-lg-12
        h2 Career Opportunities in Cybersecurity
        p.large-font
          | The field of cybersecurity offers numerous career opportunities, including roles such as:
        ul
          li Cybersecurity Analyst: Monitor and defend against security threats.
          li Ethical Hacker (Penetration Tester): Test systems for vulnerabilities and security weaknesses.
          li Security Consultant: Advise organizations on security best practices.
          li Incident Responder: Investigate and respond to security incidents.
          li Security Engineer: Design and implement security solutions.
          li Chief Information Security Officer (CISO): Oversee an organization's cybersecurity strategy.

        p.large-font
          | A career in cybersecurity is not only financially rewarding but also contributes to the protection of critical digital infrastructure.

    .row.future-of-cybersecurity
      .col-lg-12
        h2(style="color: white;") The Future of Cybersecurity
        p.large-font
          | As technology continues to evolve, the importance of cybersecurity will only grow. The field will face new challenges and opportunities, making it an exciting and dynamic career choice.

    .row.get-started
      .col-lg-12
        h2(style="color: white;") Ready to Start Your Journey in Cybersecurity?
        p.large-font
          | If you're interested in the world of cybersecurity and want to make a difference in the digital landscape, there are various educational resources and career paths available to help you get started.
